verbs.description: unmagnify (third-person singular simple present unmagnifies, present participle unmagnifying, simple past and past participle unmagnified)

entries.meaning: (transitive, rare) To make to appear smaller; to undo the magnification of.
examples: As he magnifies and unmagnifies the spectacle, picking up and putting down his glasses, he is disoriented by alternate, coexisting versions of the actress.
